Additional implementation:
**: This code is an __init__.py file that serves as the entry point for a Python package. It imports the LocationFinder class from a submodule (finder.py) and adds it to the __all__ list, making it available for import when users import the package. Its purpose is to organize and expose key components of the package without executing complex logic directly.  

```python
"""
Tools package for the MoE system.
"""

from .location import LocationFinder

__all__ = ["LocationFinder"]

